  "text": "miRNAs have various functions in tumorigenesis, which are achieved via modulation of target genes. Accordingly, miRNAs serve as biomarkers or therapeutic targets for the treatment of cancer [CITATION_1] . Particularly in drug-resistant tumors, the most determinant property for miRNA efficacy against chemotherapy resistance is the ability of the miRNAs to induce cell apoptosis. In this regard, this study focused on the role of miR-15b-5p, which we identified as being aberrantly expressed in colon cancer using the CAC model, in the chemoresistance of colon cancer.",
